gov.nih.ncats.molwitch.io

Class PushbackBufferedReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nih.ncats.molwitch.io.PushbackBufferedReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable

    public class PushbackBufferedReader
extends Object
implements AutoCloseable
    Wraps a BufferedReader so that it can "unread" lines. Unread lines are pushed into a LIFO stack. This class is NOT threadsafe.
    Author:
    katzelda

    • Method Detail

      • readLine

        public String readLine()
                throws IOException
        Read the next line. This will either be the most recently pushed back line OR the next line in the wrapped BufferedReader.
        Returns:
        the next line as a String or null if there are no more lines in the wrapped reader.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem reading the next line.

      • pushBack

        public void pushBack(String line)
        Push the given line back into the reader. If this method is called multiple times the last line pushed back is the first line returned by the next readLine() (LIFO).
        Parameters:
        line - the line to push back; can not be null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if line is null.

      • peekLine

        public String peekLine()
                throws IOException
        Read the next line and then push it back onto the stack. This is the same as: 
             
         String line = readLine();
         if(line !=null) {
             pushBack(line);
         }
         return line;
        Returns:
        the next line or null if EOF.
        Throws:
        IOException - there is a problem reading then next line.
